// RUN: triton-opt %s --nvgpu-partition-scheduling-meta="merge-correction=false merge-epilogue=false merge-epilogue-to-computation=false merge-reduction=false separate-epilogue-store=false" | FileCheck %s
//
// Regression for the PSM shared-op reduction-sink guard (T278685041 SMEM
// follow-up). For a data-partitioned (dpFactor=2) bwd reduce_dq kernel whose
// default partition IS the reduction partition (TMA-atomic reduce, no
// correction partition), preScheduleDpOps must NOT sink the shared softmax/ds
// compute chain into the reduction partition. With the guard
// (defaultPartition != reductionPartition), that chain is data-partitioned into
// the computation partitions (3/4) that consume it, while reduction keeps only
// the TMA-reduce ops. Without the guard the softmax (exp2) lands in reduction
// (partition 0), forcing reduction->computation SMEM transports of the MMA
// operands (the reduce_dq DP+fold OutOfResources root cause).
//
// Partitions: 0=reduction, 1=gemm, 2=load, 3/4=computation (the two DP halves).
//
// CHECK-LABEL: @_hstu_attn_bwd_redq
// The two per-DP softmax exp2 ops are data-partitioned into the computation
// partitions (3/4), NOT the reduction partition (0).
// CHECK-DAG: math.exp2 {{.*}}ttg.partition = array<i32: 3>
// CHECK-DAG: math.exp2 {{.*}}ttg.partition = array<i32: 4>
// The dq TMA-atomic reduce stays in the reduction partition (0).
// CHECK-DAG: ttng.async_tma_reduce {{.*}}ttg.partition = array<i32: 0>
